snippet.textDisplay: I'd really like to know a couple of things. First, was this after the December 5 percent power increase on the Model 3? And also as some people have also mentioned the Model 3's battery wasn't warmed up so its power was down by quite a bit. You can tell because the power line has dots at the end showing that power is limited. When I've tried accelerating with these dots visible you can really feel the power cut off so it would make quite a difference to the top end. Either way it would still be super close, it would just be nice to of known what the result would have been if both cars were warmed up to the maximum potential.
